meta.name: Ingest Excel data into Oracle and chat with it using Select AI and Azure OpenAI

name: AI-powered Excel data ingestion and chat with Oracle Select AI

nodes.name: Create Oracle Table
nodes.notes: Configure your Oracle Database credentials in the credentials panel

nodes.name: Split into Batches
nodes.notes: Process rows in batches of 50 for better performance

nodes.name: Insert Rows into Oracle
nodes.notes: Update the schema name to match your Oracle schema (e.g., MOVIESTREAM, ADMIN, etc.)

nodes.name: Configure Select AI Settings
nodes.notes:
⚠️ IMPORTANT: Update these values with your Azure OpenAI configuration:
- azure_resource_name: Your Azure OpenAI resource name
- azure_deployment_name: Your GPT model deployment name
- credential_name: Oracle credential name for Azure OpenAI (created via DBMS_CLOUD.CREATE_CREDENTIAL)

nodes.name: Register with Select AI
nodes.notes: Registers the uploaded table with Oracle Select AI for natural language querying

nodes.name: Configure Select AI Profile
nodes.notes:
⚠️ IMPORTANT: Update 'profileName' to match your Select AI profile name.
This should be the same profile created when you uploaded your Excel file.
Default: EXCEL_AI

nodes.name: Oracle Select AI Query
nodes.notes:
Executes natural language queries against your Excel data using Oracle Select AI.
The AI converts your question into SQL and returns the results.

nodes.name: Format Chat Response
nodes.notes: Formats the AI response for display in the chat interface

parameters.content:
## Workflow B
### How It Works
User asks question in natural language
         ↓
Chat Input captures the question
         ↓
Configure Select AI Profile (sets profile name)
         ↓
Oracle Select AI Query
- Sends question to DBMS_CLOUD_AI.GENERATE
- AI converts question to SQL
- Executes SQL against your data
- Returns formatted results
↓
Format Chat Response (cleans up the output)
↓
Display answer to user

## Configure Oracle Database Credentials

Click on any Oracle Database node (e.g., "Create Oracle Table")
Click Create New Credential
Enter your Oracle connection details:

Host: Your Oracle DB host
Database: Service name or SID
User: Database username
Password: Database password
Port: 1521 (default)


Save the credential
Apply the same credential to all Oracle nodes:

Create Oracle Table
Insert Rows into Oracle
Register with Select AI

### Update Schema Name
In the "Insert Rows into Oracle" node:
Change YOUR_SCHEMA_NAME to your actual Oracle schema (e.g., ADMIN, SCOTT, etc.)

### Configure Azure OpenAI Settings
In the "Configure Select AI Settings" node, update the selectAIConfig object

### File Size Limits
Add validation in "Validate & Normalize File"

### Registers with select AI
Registers the data with Oracle Select AI for natural language querying powered by Azure OpenAI.

### Return Success Output:
Returns { success, tableName, columns, rowCount, selectAIProfile }.
**tableName** is passed to the chat workflow so Select AI knows which table to query.

### Change Batch Size

Default: 50 rows per batch
Adjust based on your data size and database performance
**This creates the Oracle table and Select AI profile needed for querying**

### Expected Response
{
  "success": true,
  "tableName": "UPLOAD_EXCEL_20260209123456789",
  "columns": ["ID", "NAME", "AGE", "CITY", "SALARY"],
  "rowCount": 150,
  "selectAIProfile": "EXCEL_AI",
  "message": "Excel file successfully ingested and registered with Oracle Select AI",
  "nextSteps": [
    "Query your data using: SELECT AI EXCEL_AI your question here",
    "Example: SELECT AI EXCEL_AI show me the top 10 records by salary"
  ]
}
Invokes DBMS_CLOUD_AI.GENERATE with action='runsql' to translate the chat prompt into SQL, execute it on the Select AI–registered table, and return the result set.

## Workflow A Flow:
1. Webhook receives Excel file
   ↓
2. Validate & normalize file
   ↓
3. Extract data from Excel
   ↓
4. Infer schema (column names & types)
   ↓
5. Create Oracle table dynamically
   ↓
6. Insert data in batches (50 rows at a time)
   ↓
7. Configure Select AI settings
   ↓
8. Register table with Select AI
   ↓
9. Return success response
